Recorded at the Van Gelder Studio, Englewood Cliffs, New Jersey on February 15, 1967
 

Personnel:
John Coltrane, saxophone 
Alice Coltrane, piano
Jimmy Garrison, bass
Rashied Ali, drums


This was one of John Coltrane's last studio sessions, recorded in February 1967. It was not released until 1995, discovered in 1994 by his wife, Alice Coltrane, who plays the piano on the session.
Stellar Regions represents yet another of his studio explorations in which he stretched the never ending limits of free jazz, and finds him traveling on trails of cosmic dust. 
The music here is absolutely wonderful. This is an amazing collection of compositions and improvisations from a master of sound.


Straight, no chaser.
